My Lame Youtube Downloader/Converter for Windows
-----------------------------------------------------

   Quick windows util that will download youtube video's. uses "wget". All the utils are free and
open to the public. None of this is new or ground breaking. Just decided to whip one up for
windows.


- nocon
http://nocon.darkflame.net/



Files:
----------
lib             -  Required .dll's for things in bin
bin             -  Usefull (or not) Utils (wget,sed,awk,grep,strings,mplayer,ffmpeg,etc..)
get_video.bat   -  Downloads youtube flash video files (.flv)
convert_it.bat  -  Converts flash files to .mpg or .avi format (uses ffmpeg)


Usage:
----------

 get_video "youtube_url" <outfile>

ex: get_video "http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=LKJghhuyrw" myfile

  Will download the video and save it as "myfile.flv"

If you want to convert it to mpg or AVI fomat, you can use convert.bat It uses ffmpeg.exe.
It uses basic options, so you might want to play with it a bit if your not happy with the
converted video quality. Also in the bin directory is mplayer and mencoder if you prefer to
convert using that util.

Syntax: convert_it [/mpg|/avi] myfile.flv outfile

  will save to "outfile.avi" or "outfile.mpg"

Also, if you look in the get_video.bat there is the ol, "fmt=18" (format 18) for d/l high quality mp4 version's
of the video's and "fmt=6" for High Quality flash version. These are new features for youtube, so not all videos will
have this format.



